properties.Title: Low Rate Sales Tax
properties.UserDescription:
10% of transaction value to be taxed from the seller of every trade for raw goods, excluding sales from government property. If the seller is an employee of a company, the tax is actioned on the amount left untouched by the constitutional Company Income Scaling. If the initiating player is selling something but has only Self Improvement as a skill, then they are not taxed. 
There are three cases:1. the seller is neither an employee of a company nor a company himself. He pays 10% sales tax from his own pockets.2. the seller is a company itself. The company pays the reduced sales tax rate from the company's bank account.
3. the seller is an employee of a company. The company pays the reduced sales tax rate from the company's bank account.

properties.Title: High Rate Sales Tax
properties.UserDescription:
25% of transaction value to be taxed from the seller of every trade of end products, excluding sales from government property. If the seller is an employee of a company, the tax is actioned on the amount left untouched by the constitutional Company Income Scaling. If the initiating player is selling something but has only Self Improvement as a skill, then they are not taxed. 
There are three cases:1. the seller is neither an employee of a company nor a company himself. He pays 25% sales tax from his own pockets.2. the seller is a company itself. The company pays the reduced sales tax rate from the company's bank account.
3. the seller is an employee of a company. The company pays the reduced sales tax rate from the company's bank account.
